g.aria-label: 1IPv6 termination is available if you configure the load balancer in Premium Tier.2Choose external TCP/UDP network load balancing if you need to ensure that the load balancer is located in a particular region, or if you want toconfigure IPv6 load balancing (with dual-stack backends). The latter is only available for backend service-based network load balancers.3External TCP/UDP network load balancers use regional external IP addresses that are accessible by clients anywhere.4Clients in a VPC network or in a network connected to a VPC network.5The global external HTTP(S) load balancer (classic) can be configured to be effectively regional in Standard Tier.6Client source IP preservation is available in certain configurations by using the PROXY protocol.
